This paper deals with the security and verification of Bitcoin contracts, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes the use of timed automata, which is a technique commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and formal verification (cs.DL, cs.LO, cs.PL). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
